Micro apples inside a matchbox, grown near Yakutsk, Russia. 

The tiny fruits were grown on an apple tree capable of withstanding bitter winter temperatures as low as -76°F. Plants like these, which adapt to such an environment by decreasing their size, could provide a solution to food shortages in remote regions.

18-year-old Emma Raducanu celebrates reaching the US Open tennis final at Flushing Meadows, New York.

#tennis #sport #competition #usopen #newyork
